    "body": "That’s exactly what an ethers Provider has always been... Lowest-common-denominator functionality that all backends can support. It does data sanitization on input parameters (throwing on ambiguous input) and always coerces the output to known, well-defined types.\r\n\r\nIf there is missing or excessive functionality though, I’d love feedback. :)\r\n\r\nAbstractProvider: https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/blob/ethers-v5-beta/packages/abstract-provider/index.d.ts#L106",
